	<p><b>MathJax plugin</b></p>
        <p>This macro enables you to write inline equations (i.e., the equations are part of a line of text) in LaTeX or AsciiMath notation, which are then typeset using MathJax. MathJax is an open source JavaScript display engine for mathematics that works in all modern browsers.</p>
	<p>The use of AMSmath extensions is enabled.</p>
	<p><b>Examples</b>
	    <ul>
	        <li>{mathinline}\frac{x}{y}{mathinline} a nice fraction.</li>
		      <li>{mathinline}\int_{-\infty}^\infty \mbox{e}^{-x^2} \mbox{d}x{mathinline} a nice integral.</li>
	    </ul>
	</p>
